cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.DS, cs.MA 

The paper discusses social contagion and modeling cascades in networks, which are topics that fall under the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Computational Social Science). The paper also discusses the use of simulation and data analysis, which could fall under cs.CYBER (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the use of models to reduce error in estimating node thresholds, which could fall under cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
